events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Terrelle Pryor tossed three touchdown passes, Brandon Saine rushed for 103 yards and two scores and No. 2 Ohio State rolled over error-prone Marshall 42-7 on Thursday night in a tuneup for a big date with Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pryor shines as No. 2 Ohio State rolls

events.name: Florida A&M Rattlers at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Jacory Harris threw for 210 yards and three touchdowns before sitting out the second half, Leonard Hankerson caught six passes for 115 yards and two scores, and No. 13 Miami rolled past Florida A&M 45-0 Thursday night in the season-opener for both teams.

events.name: USC Trojans at Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors

headlines.description: Matt Barkley and Ronald Johnson connected on three touchdowns to make Lane Kiffin a winner in his first game as Southern California coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: USC prolific for Kiffin in debut win

headlines.description: Utah freshman Brian Blechen intercepted a pass on the first play of overtime, setting Joe Phillips for a 21-yard field goal that gave the Utes a 27-24 victory against No. 15 Pittsburgh on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah field goal in OT upends No. 15 Pitt

events.name: Presbyterian College Blue Hose at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Ted Stachitas had 160 total yards in his first college start and Wake Forest had six rushing touchdowns in a 53-13 rout of Presbyterian in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake rides six rushing TDs past Presbyterian

events.name: Southeast Missouri State Redhawks at Ball State Cardinals
Rhode Island Rams at Buffalo Bulls
Hampton Pirates at Central Michigan Chippewas
Murray State Racers at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: Darius Willis ran for two touchdowns and Ben Chappell threw for two more -- all in the first half -- as Indiana routed Towson 51-17.
headlines.shortLinkText: Willis, Chappell power Hoosiers' rout of Towson

events.name: Norfolk State Spartans at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Joe Martinek carried 20 times for 109 yards and a touchdown and Tom Savage completed 10-of-19 passes for 148 yards and a score, leading Rutgers to a 31-0 rout of Norfolk State in their season openers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers blanks Norfolk State in season opener

events.name: Shorter Hawks at Georgia State Panthers
Minnesota Golden Gophers at Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders

headlines.description: Duane Bennett rushed for a career-high 187 yards and Jon Hoese scored three touchdowns just days after deciding to make the trip to lead Minnesota to a grinding season-opening 24-17 win over Middle Tennessee.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bennett rushes for 187 yards in Minnesota win

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Quarterback Stephen Garcia and freshman tailback Marcus Lattimore each ran for two touchdowns and South Carolina coach Steve Spurrier won his 18th straight college opener 41-13 over Southern Miss.
headlines.shortLinkText: QB Garcia leads S. Carolina in rout

events.name: Florida Atlantic Owls at UAB Blazers
Northern Illinois Huskies at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Alexander Robinson rushed for 97 yards and two touchdowns and Iowa State beat Northern Illinois 27-10.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cyclones start fast, cruise past Northern Illinois

Eastern Washington Eagles at Nevada Wolf Pack
